hopobject.body: History how effective is viagra 25mg Forty years ago, Egyptian forces crossed the Suez Canal in an attempt to push the Israelis out of the Sinai Peninsula. They were backed by the air force, led by Hosni Mubarak, who became president in 1981. Initially, they failed, with the Israeli army fighting back and coming within 100 kilometres of Cairo. But the action led to the signing of the Camp David Accords and the return of Sinai to Egypt.
